Poly(aryl ether nitrile) (PEN) is a linear aromatic polymer and a high‑performance thermoplastic engineering plastic containing rigid aromatic rings and ether or sulfide linkages. It offers excellent corrosion resistance, flame‑retardancy, heat‑and‑radiation resistance, creep resistance, and electrical insulation, making it suitable for machinery manufacturing, automotive components, aerospace structures, electronics, food processing, and defense applications.

